Photo by Michal Mrozek on Unsplash记者：郑萃颖“ 万豪正在调整全球业务，许多酒店的员工将减少工作时间或暂时休假。
Photo by Michal Mrozek on Unsplash: "Marriott is restructuring its operations around the world, and many hotel workers will be working fewer hours or taking temporary vacations.
”3月18日据彭博社报道，由于疫情冲击酒店业，万豪国际集团将有数万名酒店员工进行无薪休假。
Mar 18 (Bloomberg) -- Tens of thousands of hotel workers will take unpaid leave as the hotel industry is hit by the epidemic, Bloomberg reported.
该公司的发言人说，将为这些员工保留医疗福利，并表示，万豪正在关闭一些酒店，并且在仍开放运营的酒店中，需要的员工人数变少。
A spokesman for the company said it would reserve medical benefits for the employees and said Marriott was closing some hotels and needed fewer staff in those still open.
万豪旗下管理的酒店在美国有大约13万名员工。
Marriott's hotel has about 130,000 employees in the United States.
2019年全球员工数量则为17.4万人。
The number of employees worldwide was 174,000 in 2019.
目前尚不清楚万豪对其他市场是否采取类似政策。
It is unclear whether Marriott has adopted a similar policy for other markets.
statista.com在今年2月发布的统计数据，万豪国际集团2019年的全球员工数量在17.4万人万豪在一份声明中说：“随着全球旅行限制和隔离防疫举措变得越来越普遍，我们正在经历全球住宿需求的显着下降，而且持续期限不确定。
"As global travel restrictions and quarantine measures become more common, we are experiencing a significant decline in global accommodation demand for an indefinite period," Marriott said in a statement released in February.
”“我们正在相应地调整全球业务，这意味着我们许多酒店的员工将减少工作时间或暂时休假。
"We are adjusting our global operations accordingly, which means that many of our hotel staff will be working fewer hours or taking temporary vacations.
”不过根据美国政府的失业补助申请规定，有资格申请失业补助的范围是，“并非因自己的过失而失去工作的员工”。
But the eligibility criteria for unemployment benefits under the US government's unemployment benefit program are "employees who have lost their jobs through no fault of their own."
这意味着休无薪假的员工也无法申请失业补助，可能暂时失去收入。
This means that employees on unpaid leave are also unable to apply for unemployment benefits and may temporarily lose their income.
美国政府对失业补助申请的相关规定2019年的统计数据，加上酒店加盟商，万豪在全球有7300家酒店，在酒店运营的营收上位于全球首位。
The U.S. government's 2019 statistics on claims, combined with hotel franchisees, puts Marriott in the top spot in the world, with 7,300 hotels around the world.
根据行业高管周二访问白宫时提交的一份数据，冠状病毒的爆发使美国酒店每周损失14亿美元，原因是疫情压垮了旅行需求。
The coronavirus outbreak cost US hotels $1.4 billion a week as the epidemic crushed travel demand, according to figures presented by industry executives during a visit to the White House Tuesday.
在本周二，万豪行政总裁Arne Sorenson和美高梅国际度假村集团首席执行官James Murren都在寻求政府支持。
On Tuesday, Marriott's chief executive, Arne Sorenson, and James Murren, chief executive of MGM International Resorts, both sought government support.
彭博社报道称，迪斯尼公司和希尔顿酒店集团的高管计划告诉美国政府，按当前价格计算，入住率的下降使酒店每天的客房收入损失超过2亿美元。
Bloomberg reports that executives at Disney Co. and the Hilton Group told the U.S. government that the drop in occupancy rates has cost hotels more than $200 million a day in room revenue at current prices.
希尔顿全球酒店集团CEO周二在白宫该会议上表示，希尔顿计划关闭在美国主要城市的大部分酒店。
Hilton plans to close most of its hotels in major U.S. cities, the CEO of Hilton Global Hotels Group said at a White House meeting Tuesday.
目前集团已经关闭了纽约和华盛顿的部分酒店。
The group has closed some hotels in New York and Washington.
此前在2019年第四季度及全年财报分析会议上，希尔顿高管就提到已关闭中国地区大约150家希尔顿旗下酒店，共约33000间客房。
At an analysis session in the fourth quarter of 2019 and throughout the year, Hilton executives cited the closure of about 150 Hilton hotels in China, with about 33,000 rooms.
迪士尼已经停止了海上邮轮航线，并且关闭了中国的上海、香港，以及日本东京、法国巴黎，以及美国的2家迪士尼乐园。
Disney has halted sea liner travel and closed China's Shanghai, Hong Kong, Tokyo, Paris and two Disneyland in the United States.
美高梅国际集团则因为疫情，取消了2020年的盈利预期，认为新型冠状病毒疫情使其业绩前景难以预测。
MGM International Group, because of the outbreak, cancelled the 2020 profit forecast, believing that the new coronavirus epidemic makes its performance outlook difficult to predict.
根据美国酒店住宿协会的统计，这些行业将在未来几周内不得不裁掉100万个工作岗位。
According to the American Hotel Accommodation Association, these industries will have to shed a million jobs in the next few weeks.
美国酒店住宿协会发言人Jennifer Myers表示，酒店集团的管理者将着重强调保障员工的雇佣身份，并防止永久性裁员。
Jennifer Myers, a spokesman for the American Hotel Accommodation Association, said hotel group managers would focus on protecting employees' employment status and preventing permanent layoffs.
酒店旅游业中提出的一些解决方案包括，为保留员工的公司的进行税收抵免，以及实施促进旅行的激励措施。
Some of the solutions proposed in the hotel tourism industry include tax credits for companies that retain staff and incentives to promote travel.
